Ambassador Susan Rice and U.S. Surgeon General Dr. Vivek Murthy hosted a roundtable at the White House to discuss the experiences of transgender children. Participants from states that have attacked transgender rights, including Arizona, Texas, and Virginia, shared the negative impact of these political attacks on mental health and well-being. Families emphasized the importance of parental support and access to necessary support in schools and communities for transgender children to thrive. Rice and Murthy reiterated the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to protecting the rights of transgender kids and challenging discriminatory state laws. They expressed gratitude for the families' advocacy and bravery in fighting against these laws.